<div id='about' class='about-section'>
  <h3> Our App </h3>
  <p>The National Notifiable Disease Surveillance System (NNDSS) is a program run by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) in collaboration with local, state, and federal public health centers. The program includes surveillance of notifiable infectious and noninfectious diseases. Reports are published weekly and summarized annually. Disesae reports are recieved from all 50 states, New York City, the District of Columbia, and 5 U.S. territories. This application limits data to the 50 states. We have created a map of the weekly reports organized by state. </p>
  <br>
  <a href="https://www.cdc.gov/nndss/index.html">Learn More</a>
